li.p:
Polynomials are a special type of mathematical function, or process for turning one number into another. Polynomials are functions of the form

	f(x)=a_{n}x^{n}+a_{n-1}x^{n-1}+\dots+a_{1}x^{1}+a_{0}

sums of powers of x, maybe with constant terms in front. For example, f(x)=x+1, g(x)=17x^{3}-234x+7, and h(x)=-x^{142}+1 are all polynomials. The polynomial a(x)=x^{2}+2x+3 takes the input 1 and turns it into the output 1^{2}+2(1)+3=6. All numbers which make sense to input are called the domain of the function, and the possible sensical outputs you could get are called the range.
